{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 You can manually move data in and out of a binary buffer using the \cf2 BufSet \cf1 and \cf2 BufGet\cf1  functions. This enables you to have precise control over the content of buffers, in the cases where that is needed to communicate with other software.\par
\par
In this example, data is moved in and out of a buffer when you use the\i\f1  BufSet\i0\f0  and \i\f1 BufGet \i0\f0 buttons. The data extracted should match the data that was stored.\par
\par
You can view the buffer by storing it in a text file, using the\i\f1  Blb2File\i0\f0  button, and using a hex editor to view the contents.\par
